Install and configure exim4 for sending email through gmail
	sudo apt-get install exim4
	sudo dpkg-reconfigure exim4-config
		Type: mail sent by smarthost; received via SMTP or fetchmail
		Hostname: whatever hostname you want
		Allowed IPs: 127.0.0.1 ; ::1
		Other destinations: type your hostname again
		Machines for relay: (leave it blank)
		Outgoing smarthost: smtp.gmail.com::587
		Hide local name: No
		DNS queries minimal: No
		Delivery method for local: Maildir format in home directory
		Split config: No
			
	Edit file /etc/exim4/passwd.client
		gmail-smtp.l.google.com:address@makeict.org:Password
		*.google.com:address@makeict.org:Password
		smtp.gmail.com:address@makeict.org:Password

	sudo update-exim4.conf
	sudo /etc/init.d/exim4 restart

Install upstart script
	Create symlink in /etc/init/ to alarm-alerter.conf
	
